&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Buckinghamshire Healthcare NHS Trust - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Medical Secretary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Respiratory Medicine, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stoke Mandeville Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;25 Hours/Week, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 3 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Range - £19,737 - £21,142 (pro rata)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a Medical Secretary, on a 12-month Fixed Term Contract (maternity cover) to work as part of a Team of Medical Secretaries in the Department of Respiratory Medicine at Stoke Mandeville Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible to the Team Leader for Integrated Medicine and your main responsibility will be to assist in providing a comprehensive, confidential and quality Medical Secretarial Service within the Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of word processing and audio-typing is essential, as is the ability to demonstrate a sound knowledge of medical terminology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will ideally have previous NHS experience in a similar setting and will be familiar with Trust systems, such as Medway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion, or to arrange a visit, please contact Karen Robinson on 07826 944262.&lt;/p&gt;
